If you’ve built an LLM agent that does anything non-trivial, you’ve hit this moment: “Cool… but how do I make it do the thing later, reliably, and without losing its place?” That “later + reliably + resume” trio is basically: - Durable execution (survive crashes, restarts, deploys, flaky APIs, timeouts) - Scheduling (do work at a specific time / cron / interval)
- Queueing (do work asynchronously) LangGraph and Cloudflare Agents are both among your options, but they solve the problem from different layers of the stack. - LangGraph is a workflow/orchestration framework for building stateful agent logic, with checkpointing and “resume from where you left off” baked into the execution model. Press enter or click to view image in full size - Cloudflare Agents is an edge/serverless runtime + SDK for building stateful, real-time agents on top of Durable Objects, with built-in task queueing and scheduling, and optional Workflows for true durable, multi-step background runs. ## Written by Agent Native

